f **Cramer's rule** that allows us to solve some instances of `A ⬝ x = b` even\nif the determinant is not a unit. A sufficient (but still not necessary) condition is that `A.det`\ndivides `b`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/Adjugate.lean#L305-L308","name":"Matrix.adjugate_smul","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/Adjugate.html#Matrix.adjugate_smul","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/Adjugate.lean#L298-L302","name":"Matrix.adjugate_mul","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/Adjugate.html#Matrix.adjugate_mul","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/Adjugate.lean#L292-L295","name":"Matrix.mul_adjugate","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/Adjugate.html#Matrix.mul_adjugate","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/Adjugate.lean#L286-L289","name":"Matrix.mul_adjugate_apply","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/Adjugate.html#Matrix.mul_adjugate_apply","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/Adjugate.lean#L271-L283","name":"Matrix.cramer_eq_adjugate_mulVec","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/Adjugate.html#Matrix.cramer_eq_adjugate_mulVec","doc":"Since the map `b ↦ cramer A b` is linear in `b`, it must be multiplication by some matrix. This\nmatrix is `A.adjugate`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/Adjugate.lean#L264-